{"id":"b46f96165f8a73d0145b19e1184d628eb5f7e6b4","axis":"silent","repo":"pnpm/pnpm","sha":"b46f96165f8a73d0145b19e1184d628eb5f7e6b4","parsed":{"files":[{"path":".changeset/windows-kill-tracked-process-trees.md","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@","+---","+\"@pnpm/exec.lifecycle\": patch","+\"@pnpm/exec.commands\": patch","+\"pnpm\": patch","+---","+","+Fixed orphaned child processes on Windows when pnpm exits on an error while commands spawned by `pnpm exec` or `pnpm dlx` are still running (for example, when one project's command fails during `pnpm --recursive exec`). The PIDs of these commands are now recorded when they are spawned and their whole process trees are terminated with `taskkill` on an error exit. Previously the cleanup relied on enumerating the system process list, which is so slow on Windows that the enumeration hit its timeout and the cleanup was silently skipped [#12406](https://github.com/pnpm/pnpm/issues/12406)."],"additions":7,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"cspell.json","lines":["@@ -257,6 +257,7 @@","     \"partialmatch\",","     \"pathext\",","     \"pegjs\",","+    \"pids\",","     \"pidtree\",","     \"pify\",","     \"pkgname\",","@@ -384,12 +385,14 @@","     \"syncer\",","     \"syscall\",","     \"syscalls\",","+    \"systemroot\",","     \"szia\",","     \"tabtab\",","     \"taffydb\",","     \"taiki\",","     \"tarballtemplate\",","     \"Tarjan\",","+    \"taskkill\",","     \"teambit\",","     \"tempy\",","     \"testcase\",","@@ -417,6 +420,7 @@","     \"unreviewed\",","     \"unskip\",","     \"unstar\",","+    \"untracks\",","     \"usecase\",","     \"userconfig\",","     \"userprofile\",","@@ -425,8 +429,11 @@","     \"valign\",","     \"versionless\",","     \"vuln\",","+    \"wbem\",","     \"webauth\",","     \"webcontainer\",","+    \"windir\",","+    \"windowspowershell\",","     \"winst\",","     \"workleap\",","     \"worktree\","],"additions":7,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"pnpm-lock.yaml","lines":["@@ -7670,